<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<subsection xml:id="testing_procedures">
  <title>Testing Procedures</title>
    <p>
    <ul>
      <li>The tests are given face-to-face in a classroom or with a proctor (if away from campus) and <alert>not</alert>
         online; they are traditional exams worked on paper.</li>
      <li>
        <p>
        Students enrolled in an online section are responsible for finding an approved proctor;
        however, they may take the exam on-campus if preferred.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
            Students testing in Ruston, LA may use only the following locations (besides course
             instructor):
             <ul>
                <li>Louisiana Tech Library</li>
                <li>Testing and Disability Services (TDS) - for students with documented accommodations.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
            Students must use an <alert>official testing center</alert> (independent or affiliated with a college/university)
             if one exists within <alert>40 miles</alert> of their location. If no testing center
              is available, a <alert>public or college librarian</alert> who offers proctoring services
               may be used.
               <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Any exceptions must be approved by the COES Proctor Coordinator, Alexis Dixon (adixon@latech.edu).
                    </p>
                </li>
               </ul>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
            Students must complete the <alert>Student Proctor Information Form</alert> on Canvas <alert>one week before the first exam</alert>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
            Each proctor will be approved by the Proctor Coordinator.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
            Students must take exams on the scheduled date unless the <alert>instructor pre-approves an alternate date</alert>.
             Students must also notify the proctor of any approved changes.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
            Students are responsible for following the time limits set for each exam.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </p>
</subsection>